00:15:14,249 --> 00:15:15,691
And then, of course, says the opposite.

146
00:15:15,791 --> 00:15:20,797
When non-greed arises in a person, is it for his welfare or his harm?

147
00:15:21,076 --> 00:15:22,198
Says for his welfare.

148
00:15:22,339 --> 00:15:26,303
Kalama is a person without greed, not overcome by greed.

149
00:15:26,624 --> 00:15:35,354
His mind, not obsessed by it, does not destroy life, take what is not given, transgress with another's wife or speak falsehood.

150
00:15:35,855 --> 00:15:38,378
Nor does he encourage others to do likewise.

151
00:15:38,717 --> 00:15:41,721
Will that lead to his welfare and happiness for a long time?

152
00:15:42,142 --> 00:15:42,822
Yes, Panty.

153
00:15:44,423 --> 00:15:48,527
And of course, the same with non-hatred and the same with non-delusion.

154
00:15:49,268 --> 00:15:52,910
The Buddha does more often than not prefer the negative.

155
00:15:53,572 --> 00:15:59,418
So if there's not greed, then there must be all those qualities that are not greed.

156
00:15:59,798 --> 00:16:13,130
So instead of saying, you know, generosity and all that, trying to find words for all that, he just simply says where there's no greed, then there's not that possibility of making mistakes that greed would lead you to.

157
00:16:17,195 --> 00:16:27,264
So then when he's cleared the path, when he said, look, it's up to you to decide what is to your welfare, to the welfare of others, etc.

158
00:16:28,105 --> 00:16:42,561
Then he goes, Calamas, that noble disciple who is thus devoid of longing, devoid of ill will, unconfused, clearly comprehending, ever mindful.

159
00:16:42,912 --> 00:16:55,111
dwells pervading one quarter with his mind imbued with loving kindness, with a mind imbued with compassion, with a mind imbued with altruistic love, with a mind imbued with equanimity.

160
00:16:56,534 --> 00:17:06,912
And the second quarter, the third and the fourth quarter, thus above and below, across and everywhere, and to all as to himself, he dwells pervading the entire world,

161
00:17:07,162 --> 00:17:14,977
with a mind imbued with equanimity, vast, exalted, measureless, without enmity, without ill will.

162
00:17:15,438 --> 00:17:27,381
So that's a beautiful way of saying to people that once you stop all this negative stuff, the mind naturally moves towards these very beautiful mental states.

163
